heading_context: If you applied online with a digital photo
chunks.html_content:
How you track your passport application depends on how you applied for it.

You can track your application immediately if you applied online and your application reference begins with ‘PEX’.
chunks.plain_content:
Track your passport application
If you applied online with a digital photo
How you track your passport application depends on how you applied for it.
You can track your application immediately if you applied online and your application reference begins with ‘PEX’.

heading_context: If you applied at the Post Office using the Digital Check and Send service
chunks.html_content:
After applying at a Post Office branch you can track your application.

You used this service if:

  • the Post Office took your photo for you
  • your application reference begins with ‘POD’
chunks.plain_content:
Track your passport application
If you applied at the Post Office using the Digital Check and Send service
After applying at a Post Office branch you can track your application.
You used this service if:

  the Post Office took your photo for you
  your application reference begins with ‘POD’

heading_context: If you filled in a paper form
chunks.html_content:
Call the Passport Adviceline to track your application if you applied for your passport:

  • by filling in a paper form
  • at the Post Office using Check and Send

When you call, select option 1 and enter either the:

  • 10-digit barcode number from your application form
  • 9-digit number on your receipt if you applied at the Post Office
